I feel like I’m finally getting to a place of acceptance. This photo was taken last spring with @rafael.avcioglu when I was really looking at myself and honoring my body and all that I’ve been through. Five years ago looked really different for me. I was dreaming I would be in the place I am now, and although it isn’t perfect, I feel like the most authentic version of myself and I’m continuing to explore that too. Show up as you are and you will find the people who celebrate you. Let’s do it again @rafa.film PS @whitneyotte always has the most stunning apartment to shoot in! Thank you for seeing me in my truth 🤍

Recently I was featured in Voyage Utah Magazine @voyageutah under Local Stories “Rising Stars.” I have to admit I’ve been hesitant to share this article because I get really vulnerable and deep into my story. Today I reminded myself that my goal is to celebrate others for being vulnerable. With that being said, I hope you take the time to read the article so that it can potentially spark a conversation between us about a life experience or how you enjoy a good wiggle aka your creative outlet. The link is in my bio under “Voyage Magazine” Photo credits are Michelle Coppini @michellecoppini of Remnant Photography, Brittany Heiland of @forgetmeknot_photos and Jiyang Chen @jiyangc among others listed #voyagemagazine

I was sick or injured four months out of 2023 and on our way back from Utah, our car broke down. Even without a car and a broken leg, I’ve never been happier. As we were driving back in a rental all I could think was: I have everything I need right here. Grateful for my supportive partner and our strong bond, I realize that health, happiness, and our pets are all that truly matter. I’ve also developed a newfound appreciation for my body and the integral role movement plays in my life. No specific New Year's resolutions, although I eagerly anticipate moving, recovering, and strengthening connections with loved ones in the coming year. Oh yea, my hair is changing again too 🙃
